# 🧠 OS Concept 1: Distributed Systems Basics

## 1️⃣ Simple Idea

A distributed system =

👉 multiple computers working together as one system.

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

Food delivery company 🍔

* one handles orders
* one handles payment
* one handles delivery

Different systems cooperate.

---

## ⚙️ Why Use Distributed Systems?

✔ scalability
✔ reliability
✔ fault tolerance
✔ performance

---

## Examples

* cloud platforms
* banking systems
* social media

---

## 🔗 Connection

Load balancing and fault tolerance from Day 34 are important here.

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why distributed systems are scalable?**

👉 Because workload is shared across multiple machines.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="9y4w1k"
Distributed = many computers, one system
```

