# ⚙️ COA Concept 3: Hyperthreading

---

## 1️⃣ Simple Idea

One physical CPU core behaves like multiple logical cores.

---

## Why?

To improve CPU utilization.

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

One worker handling two tasks smartly by switching quickly.

---

## ⚙️ How It Works

When one thread waits:

👉 CPU uses unused resources for another thread.

---

## 🔗 Connection

Uses:

* concurrency
* latency hiding

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why hyperthreading improves performance?**

👉 Better utilization of CPU resources during stalls.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="7d3m1v"
One core acts like two
```

---

# ⚙️ COA Concept 4: SIMD (Single Instruction Multiple Data)

🔥 Very important in AI and graphics.

---

## 1️⃣ Simple Idea

One instruction operates on multiple data values simultaneously.

---

## Example

Add multiple numbers together:

```text id="t7w8qf"
A1+A2+A3+A4
```

in parallel.

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

Teacher giving same instruction to whole class.

---

## Uses

* graphics
* AI
* image processing
* scientific computing

---

## 🔗 Connection

SIMD came from Flynn’s classification earlier.

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why SIMD useful in AI/graphics?**

👉 Because same operation is performed on large datasets simultaneously.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="r5x1pk"
One instruction, many data
```

